Bony projection that is the posterolaterally oriented projection on the ventral region of the mesethmoid. Mesethmoid ventral diverging lamellae are paired and posteriorly contact the lateral ethmoid bones.

definition.value: Reference: Weitzman 1962.

value.value: Process that is the posteriorly oriented, paired projection of the basipterygium.
Foramen that is located in the scapula. The scapular foramen is paired and formed by a ring of bone.

definition.value: Weitzman 1962.

value.value: Anatomical space that is an opening in a bone, usually for passage of blood vessels or nerves.
Foramen that is located in the coracoid.
Anatomical structure that is a membranous gap between bones of the skull.
Fontanel that is located between the contralateral frontals and anterior to the epiphyseal bar.
Fontanel that is located posterior to the epiphyseal bar, and typically located between the contralateral frontals and parietals (if present) and bordered posteriorly by the supraoccipital.
Foramen through which branches of cranial nerves V (trigeminal) and VII (facial) exit.

definition.value: i]In some vertebrates there are separate trigeminal foramen and facial foramen.

value.value: Foramen through which cranial nerve VIII (auditory) exits.

definition.value: Reference: Weitzman 1962.

value.value: Anatomical space that is a concavity, shallow depression, or groove on a bone.
Anatomical space within a bone in which teeth develop.
Replacement tooth trench that is located in the premaxilla.
Replacement tooth trench that is located in the dentary.
Bony projection located on the anteroventral region of the mesethmoid which articulates with the premaxilla.

definition.value: Synonyms: mesethmoid lateral wing (Zanata and Vari 2005) lateral ethmoid wing (Weitzman 1962) premaxillary articular process (Fink and Fink 1996).

value.value: Foramen through which the superficial ophthalmic nerve passes.
Joint that articulates the dentary and anguloarticular. Dentary-anguloarticular joint is paired.
Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the sixth centrum.
Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fifth centrum.
The pre-narial cartilage is a cartilage that is located anterior to the anterior naris.

definition.value: Chen 1994.

value.value: Fossa where the exoccipital forms the medial portion and the epioccipital forms the lateral margin.

definition.value: Chen 1994 gives these two synonyms: "temporal fossa", Gauba 1967; and "temporal groove", Mahajan 1966.

value.value: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1 is the leading or marginal ray of the fin and articulates with the scapula.  Lepidotrichium 1 is commonly segmented but unbranched but occasionally may be a massive strong unsegmented element (e.g., spine).
Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the second most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.
